## SQL Interface

### Option A: COPY TO (preferred)

```sql
-- Export query results to PLINK 2 fileset
COPY (
    SELECT CHROM, POS, ID, REF, ALT, genotypes
    FROM read_pfile('input')
    WHERE CHROM = '22'
) TO 'output/chr22' (FORMAT plink);

-- Export with explicit format version
COPY (
    SELECT * FROM read_pfile('input')
) TO 'output/filtered' (FORMAT plink, VERSION 2);

-- Export to PLINK 1 format (.bed/.bim/.fam)
COPY (
    SELECT * FROM read_pfile('input')
) TO 'output/legacy' (FORMAT plink, VERSION 1);

-- Export after sample QC
COPY (
    SELECT * FROM read_pfile('cohort',
        orient := 'variant',
        samples := (SELECT list(IID) FROM plink_missing('cohort.pgen',
            mode := 'sample') WHERE F_MISS < 0.05))
) TO 'output/qc_passed' (FORMAT plink);
```

### Option B: Table function (fallback)

```sql
-- Write a filtered fileset
SELECT write_pfile('output/chr22',
    pgen := 'input.pgen', pvar := 'input.pvar', psam := 'input.psam',
    region := '22');
```

