## COPY TO Integration

DuckDB extensions can register custom COPY functions via
`ExtensionLoader::RegisterCopyFunction()`. This requires implementing:

1. **CopyFunction**: Bind, InitLocal, InitGlobal, Sink, Combine, Finalize
2. **CopyToBindInput**: Parse format options (VERSION, etc.)
3. **Sink function**: Receive DataChunks, accumulate/write data

The COPY interface receives arbitrary query output, so the implementation
must validate that the input schema matches expected PLINK format (requires
genotype column, variant metadata columns, etc.).

### Input Schema Requirements

The COPY function expects specific column names:

| Column | Required | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| CHROM | Yes | Chromosome |
| POS | Yes | Position |
| ID | No | Variant ID (auto-generated if missing) |
| REF | Yes | Reference allele |
| ALT | Yes | Alternate allele |
| genotypes | Yes | ARRAY(TINYINT, N) or LIST(TINYINT) genotype column |

Sample metadata (FID, IID, SEX) is inferred from the genotype array size
and optionally provided via format options.

