## Testing

### Roundtrip Tests

The primary validation strategy is roundtrip: read → filter → write → read
back → compare.

```sql
require plinking_duck

# Write and read back variant metadata
COPY (SELECT * FROM read_pfile('test/data/pgen_example'))
TO '__TEST_DIR__/roundtrip' (FORMAT plink);

query I
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM read_pvar('__TEST_DIR__/roundtrip.pvar');
----
4

# Genotypes survive roundtrip
query I
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM (
    SELECT a.genotypes AS orig, b.genotypes AS copy
    FROM read_pfile('test/data/pgen_example') a
    JOIN read_pfile('__TEST_DIR__/roundtrip') b ON a.ID = b.ID
    WHERE a.genotypes != b.genotypes
);
----
0

# Filtered export has correct variant count
COPY (
    SELECT * FROM read_pfile('test/data/large_example')
    WHERE CHROM = '1'
) TO '__TEST_DIR__/chr1_only' (FORMAT plink);

query I
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM read_pvar('__TEST_DIR__/chr1_only.pvar');
----
1000
```

### Negative Tests

```sql
require plinking_duck

# Missing required columns
statement error
COPY (SELECT 1 AS x) TO '__TEST_DIR__/bad' (FORMAT plink);
----
(error: missing required columns)
```

